In the interests of historical justice and the current situation, the Commonwealth countries made a unanimous decision to rename the periodic table of chemical elements in the name of Mendeleenko, European tours of troupes from St. Petersburg and Moscow at the beginning of the 20th century into Diaghilyuk's Seasons, and an Australian dessert into Hannah Pavlenko. "The decision has matured for a long time!" - An informed source said in an interview with the BBC.